  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 621511 (Medical Laboratories) total $146M for FY2026 to date. The market has recorded 1,969 awards so far, with an average award size of $74.2K and obligations down 68.2% year over year. Obligations have declined from earlier pandemic-era peaks: FY21 was $2.6B, FY22 was $1.7B, FY23 was $418M, FY24 was $398M, FY25 was $460M, and FY26 to date is $146M. These figures are contract obligations and the current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). For FY2026 to date, the Department of Veterans Affairs shows the largest buying activity at $197M, followed by the Department of Defense at $78.7M and the Department of Justice at $7M. Leading vendors for the current fiscal year to date include QUEST DIAGNOSTICS INCORPORATED at $51.5M, LABORATORY CORPORATION OF AMERICA at $43M, and COLLEGE OF AMERICAN PATHOLOGISTS at $9.7M. The distribution of obligations and the decline year over year indicate a materially smaller federal medical laboratory contracting year so far compared with FY21 and FY22.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal spending trended over recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations peaked in FY21 at $2.6B and fell to $1.7B in FY22 before dropping to $418M in FY23. FY24 obligations were $398M, FY25 was $460M, and FY26 to date is $146M, representing a down 68.2% year-over-year change for the current fiscal year to date."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the major buyers and suppliers in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top buying agency for FY2026 to date is the Department of Veterans Affairs at $197M, followed by the Department of Defense at $78.7M and the Department of Justice at $7M. Top suppliers are QUEST DIAGNOSTICS INCORPORATED at $51.5M, LABORATORY CORPORATION OF AMERICA at $43M, and COLLEGE OF AMERICAN PATHOLOGISTS at $9.7M."
      }
    ]
